2.8 &NETS.
:SKRSLUT.
.br
&NETS. Denmark A/S, CVR No. &PBSCVR. is the company that operates
Betalingsservice. As payment service provider, &NETS. is
subject to supervision by the Danish
Financial Supervisory Authority.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.9 Return
:SKRSLUT.
.br
Return of a payment means that the amount is returned from the creditor's
account to the customer's account. The customer or &BANKNAVN. may request a
transfer of a payment already executed if the conditions are met, see
clause 8.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.10 Betalingsservice debtor agreement (BS debtor agreement)
:SKRSLUT.
.br
A debtor agreement is an agreement between the customer and
&BANKNAVN. authorising the customer to pay bills through Betalingsservice.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS10.
:FED.
3. Registration for Betalingsservice
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
:FED.
3.1 The BS debtor agreement
:SKRSLUT.
.br
It is a condition for using Betalingsservice that the customer has
concluded a BS debtor agreement with &BANKNAVN.. If the customer wishes to
use Betalingsservice, the customer must contact &BANKNAVN..
.br
&BANKNAVN. is not obliged to conclude a BS debtor agreement with the
customer but will make an individual assessment as to whether the customer
may use Betalingsservice.
.br
Once the customer has a BS debtor agreement, the customer may give BS
mandates.
.br
If the customer has no BS debtor agreement, &BANKNAVN. is entitled to
return payments already effected and cancel BS mandates in accordance with
the provisions set out in clause 8.3.
.sp 3mm
:FED.
3.2 Rules
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The BS debtor agreement obliges the customer to comply with the General
conditions for Betalingsservice debtors.
